1.Creating a table

	CREATE TABLE Users(
		name VARCHAR(128),
		email VARCHAR(128)
	)

2.Inserting data

	INSERT INTO Users(name,email) VALUES ('name','emailID')

3.Deleting data

	DELETE FROM Users WHERE email ='emailID'

4.Updating data

	UPDATE Users SET name='name' WHERE email = 'emailID'

5.Retrieving Records: Select
	* refers to column - here * means all column

	SELECT * FROM Users
	SELECT * FROM Users WHERE email='emailID'

6. Sorting with ORDER BY
	you can add an ORDER BY clause to SELECT statements to get the results in 
	ascending or descending order

	SELECT * FROM Users ORDER BY email
	SELECT * FROM Users ORDER BY name


